# mxup

**Declarative tmux session manager with reconciliation.** Given a YAML
config, `mxup up` brings the live tmux session into agreement with it:
creates missing windows, restarts crashed ones, removes undeclared ones,
and leaves healthy processes alone. Idempotent; re-running `up` is safe.

## Layout

- `bin/mxup` — thin entrypoint → `Mxup::CLI`.
- `lib/mxup/` — one concern per file: `config`, `tmux` (shell wrapper),
  `launcher` (per-window scripts), `pane_resolver`, `reconciler`,
  `layout_manager`, `status_view`, `exec_runner`, `graceful_stop`,
  `process_probe`, `runner` (facade).
- `test/unit_test.rb` — pure logic; stubs `Mxup::Tmux` via `TestHelpers::TmuxStubs`.
- `test/integration_test.rb` — private tmux server via `TMUX_TMPDIR` + `tmux -f`.

## Commands

`up [name]` (default), `status`, `down`, `restart [name:]w1,w2`,
`layout [name] <layout>` (PIDs survive), `target [name:]<window>`,
`exec -t <target> "<cmd>"` (runs, waits, captures output, exits with rc).
All accept `-f <path>` and `--dry-run` where meaningful.

## Config shape

```yaml
session: my-proj
windows:
  web:
    root: ~/app
    command: npm run dev
    wait_for: localhost:5432     # shorthand = tcp; also {http,path,script}
    env: { NODE_ENV: production }
layouts:                          # optional
  full:
    svc: { panes: [db, web], split: even-horizontal }
```

## Reconciliation contract

When touching `reconciler.rb` / `layout_manager.rb`, preserve:
- missing → created; extra → killed with warning; idle → command re-sent;
  healthy → untouched.
- Layout switches flatten panes then regroup, preserving PIDs.
- `Mxup::Tmux.break_pane` must pin `-t <session>:` or windows leak into
  the caller's session.

## Tests

`rake unit` (~0.4s, no tmux), `rake integration` (~7s, private server),
`rake` (both). Integration shortens production sleeps via
`Mxup::Runner.interrupt_delay` and `Mxup::GracefulStop.round_interval` —
don't reintroduce hardcoded sleeps; plumb a knob through instead.
